    slug: "tohfat-ul-muslim-sharah-sahih-muslim-urdu-8-volumes-set",
    description: `Tohfat ul Muslim is a comprehensive Urdu commentary (sharah) on Sahih Muslim, one of the six most authentic hadith collections in Islamic literature. Published as an 8-volume set, this monumental work represents years of dedicated scholarship aimed at making the profound content of Imam Muslim ibn al-Hajjaj's renowned hadith compilation accessible to Urdu-speaking audiences worldwide. Sahih Muslim ranks alongside Sahih al-Bukhari as the most authoritative source of Prophetic traditions, and this commentary ensures that its treasures are unlocked for readers who may not have access to classical Arabic scholarship.

The commentary covers every aspect of hadith sciences that a serious student or scholar requires. Each hadith is presented with its full chain of narration (isnad) followed by the text (matn), accompanied by detailed explanatory notes that clarify difficult vocabulary, contextualize the circumstances under which each saying was uttered, and draw connections between related narrations throughout the collection. The commentator addresses the classification of each hadith, explaining why Imam Muslim included it in his Sahih and discussing any variations in wording between different narrators. Where multiple narrations of the same incident exist, the commentary presents them together with comparative analysis, enabling readers to appreciate the depth and precision of hadith scholarship.

The 8-volume structure organizes the hadith systematically according to the chapters established by Imam Muslim himself, covering topics ranging from faith (iman) and purification (taharah) to prayer (salah), fasting (sawm), pilgrimage (hajj), marriage (nikah), trade, warfare, and eschatology. This comprehensive scope makes the set a complete reference library for Islamic jurisprudence and theology. The Urdu translation maintains the precision of the original Arabic while using language that is clear and scholarly, making it suitable for madrasah curricula, university-level Islamic studies, and advanced personal research.

The physical production of this 8-volume set reflects its scholarly importance, with durable binding and clear typesetting that accommodates extended study sessions. Each volume includes a table of contents for quick reference, and the set as a whole provides a seamless reading experience across all eight books. Scholars, imams, students of Islamic sciences, and serious household libraries will find Tohfat ul Muslim to be an indispensable companion for understanding the authentic Sunnah of the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) in its full depth and breadth.`,
    metaDescription: "Tohfat ul Muslim Sharah Sahih Muslim Urdu 8 Volumes Set – comprehensive Urdu commentary on Sahih Muslim hadith collection with detailed explanations."
